I performed statistical analysis using SPSS to examine the correlation between rehabilitation service utilization and return-to-work duration, applying descriptive statistics, cross-tabulation, t-tests, and multiple regression analysis.
The study showed that individual health status and economic urgency have a more significant impact on return-to-work duration than the mere provision of rehabilitation services.
